<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3694746>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Dibunostoma reversum (Harmer, 1926). A. Colony, showing autozooids, kenozooids (arrowhead), and autozooid (arrow) with orificial closure plate giving rise to overgrowth layer, VNMN-0213. B. Autozooids, showing shape of orifice, VNMN-0213. C. Overgrowth layer arising from autozooid with orificial closure plate, VNMN-0213. D. Interzooidal avicularium, one of two daughter zooids at column branch point, VNMN-0273. E. Autozooids, with one vicarious avicularium, VNMN- 0274. F. Kenozooids at colony margin, VNMN-0275. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 500 µm; D, 200 µm; E, F, 250 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3694746/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

